# Xectec Design System вЂ” Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build a centralized, enterprise-grade, reusable UI component library (`@xectec/ui`) as a **monorepo** with:
- Design tokens (CSS Variables)
- React component library
- Storybook documentation
- Vite library-mode build
- Next.js integration validation

---

## Architecture Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **My proposed approach vs. the plan document:**
> The plan document is high-level. Below are specific technical decisions I'll make that you should review before I proceed.

| Decision | Plan Says | My Proposal |
|---|---|---|
| **Monorepo tool** | Just says "packages/" folder | **pnpm workspaces** (fastest, no node_modules duplication, great for monorepos) |
| **Package scope** | `@company/ui` | **`@xectec/ui`** (your company name) |
| **Token format** | CSS variables | CSS variables **+ a typed JS/TS token object** so apps can use tokens in JS too |
| **Testing** | Unit tests required | **Vitest** (native Vite integration, much faster than Jest) |
| **Dark mode** | Future scalability | **Built-in from Day 1** via CSS variable token swap вЂ” costs nothing to set up now |
| **Accessibility** | Mentioned | Radix UI primitives under the hood for Modal (focus trap, ARIA) вЂ” components remain fully styled by us |

